The paper deals with entity resolution author disambiguation in bibliographic networks, which involves analyzing co-authorship data to identify authors with similar topological characteristics. This is a common problem in information retrieval (IR) and database (DB) systems, as well as in social network analysis (SI), system dynamics (SD), and systems and control (SY). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.IR and cs.DB, followed by cs.SI, cs.SD, and cs.SY.
